  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "A Mastodon instance is a server running Mastodon software, hosting user accounts and their posts. Each instance operates independently with its own rules, moderation policies, and community norms, but participates in the fediverse by federating with other instances through ActivityPub.\nUsers on one instance can follow and interact with users on any federated instance. The instance administrator controls which other instances to federate with: they can silence (hide from public timelines but allow individual follows) or suspend (block entirely) instances whose moderation standards or content do not align with their community\u0026rsquo;s norms.\n",
